Italy May Delay Nuclear Program, Environment Minister Tells Ansa

-- B y   A l e s s a n d r a   M i g l i a c c i o
-- 
2011-03-19T15:12:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-19/italy-may-delay-nuclear-program-environment-minister-tells-ansa.html
Italy may reconsider or delay its
nuclear program in light of damage to reactors in  Japan  that has
engineers struggling to contain radiation, Italian Environment
Minister Stefania Prestigiacomo told newswire Ansa.  “Prospects for nuclear energy are looking more distant,”
she told the newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alessandra Migliaccio in Rome at 
 amigliaccio@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Kennedy at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net . 